HEADWORD: Odalisque
<hw>O`da`lisque"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
Turk. <ets>odaliq</ets> chambermaid, fr. <ets>oda</ets> chamber,
room.]</ety> <def>A female slave or concubine in the harem of the
Turkish sultan.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>odahlic</asp>,
<asp>odalisk</asp>, and <asp>odalik</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

